{
  "texts": [
    "Chain of thought and chain of thought with self-consistency prompting techniques have shown their potential to enhance the performance of LLMs in multiple non-nutrition studies by enabling chatbots to address complex reasoning tasks [30] [31] [32].",
    "Retrieval augmented prompting models have also indicated their effectiveness in mitigating LLMs hallucination problems across generic scenarios.",
    "We hypothesize that these step-by-step reasoning techniques and retrieval models can surpass zero-shot prompting techniques, especially in breaking down complex nutritional questions, handling uncertainties by providing external information, and enabling better decision-making [33] [34] [35] [36].",
    "It is essential to investigate the impact of these prompting techniques on LLMs performance in handling various nutrition-related queries.",
    "Third, previous work merely focused on the overall accuracy of LLMs responses."
  ]
}